Tognum to Reduce Size of Management Board, Coers to Become CEO

-- B y   M a r i a j o s e   V e r a
-- 
2011-09-20T06:34:59Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-09-20/tognum-to-reduce-size-of-management-board-coers-to-become-ceo.html
Tognum AG (TGM)  will reduce the size of
its management board as of Oct. 1, the company said in an e-
mailed statement today. Joachim Coers will become chief
executive officer and Dieter Royal will succeed Coers as chief
financial officer. Management board member Christof von
Branconi, currently responsible for onsite energy and
components, is leaving the company for personal reasons, Tognum
said.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Mariajose Vera at 
 mvera1@bloomberg.net  